It's a client side scripting language. Runs on the client browser.


Quickstart:
============
Import JavaScript into html pages.
1. Using script tag.
<body>
  <script>alert("write you code")</script>
<body>

2. Pass the JavaScript file.
<body>
  <script src="javascript.js"/>





Place the javascript wherever required in you html page. HTML page will get execute in sequence. If you need to exucute js after page loaded, then put
it at the end of the html page. Also, its a best practice to put the javascript in the bottom.


Variable:
============
Create a variable:
var x=1
var name="test"
var y="30"      => type is string. it will not recognize it as int.(x+y give 130)

Arrays:
===========
var mylist = ['apple','banana']
myList[0]

mylist.forEach(function(value,index) {
   console.log(value,index);
   });

Functions:
===========
alert("test")    => pop up dialog box with "test" in it.
var name = prompt('enter your wish')         => open dialog box and ask for user input. Used to get input from end user.

User defined functions:
=======================

function test(){
alert("function test");
}

go();                 =>function calling statement.
